description:
These benchmarks are translations from the TPTP Library (Thousands of
Problems for Theorem Provers), see http://www.cs.miami.edu/~tptp/

The TPTP is maintained by Geoff Sutcliffe, and he contributed this
selection of benchmarks to SMT-LIB.

selection of benchmarks to SMT-LIB.

These benchmarks are translations from the TPTP Library (Thousands of
Problems for Theorem Provers), see http://www.cs.miami.edu/~tptp/

The TPTP is maintained by Geoff Sutcliffe, and he contributed this
selection of benchmarks to SMT-LIB.

An Optimal Algorithm for Mutual Exclusion in Computer Networks. Glenn Ricart and Ashok K. Agrawala. Communications of the ACM Vol.: 24 Number: 1. This is a benchmark of the haRVey theorem prover. It was translated to SMT-LIB by Leonardo  de Moura

GRASShopper benchmarks.
  Authors: Ruzica Piskac, Thomas Wies, and Damien Zufferey
  URL: http://cs.nyu.edu/wies/software/grasshopper
  See also: GRASShopper - Complete Heap Verification with Mixed Specifications. In TACAS 2014, pages 124-139.

  If this benchmark is satisfiable, GRASShopper reports the following error message:
  tests/spl/sls/sls_copy.spl:50:5-6:An invariant might not be maintained by a loop in procedure copy
  tests/spl/sls/sls_copy.spl:36:16:Related location: This is the loop invariant that might not be maintained
